&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HULL UNIVERSITY TEACHING HOSPITALS NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Locum Consultant Emergency Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emergency Medicine Health Group&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hull Royal Infirmary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;10 PAs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time or LTFT (6 months and extendable)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During the Covid pandemic, many doctors, especially locums prefer stability, consistency and the benefits of working for an NHS organisation. We would like to reach out and support that specific group. If you have just finished training and want to try a locum post or have been a locum for a while and want to try a change, this is your opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Locum Consultant in Emergency Medicine. The successful applicant would join a team of 18 consultants in Hull.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Emergency Department is situated at Hull Royal Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Major Trauma Centre (Adults)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Newly built modern department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Large Adult Resus and separate Paediatric Resus Areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paediatric EM training centre&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annualised Rota with Self- Rostering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great team (18 consultants and over 100 nursing/auxiliary staff)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Beautiful City, Great Schools, Spectacular Landscape eastyorkshhire.co.uk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ED in Hull is an accredited Major Trauma Centre for adults and a Trauma Unit for children. It is classified as a Large ED, seeing more than 139,000 attendances per annum. It serves the whole of the Hull and East Riding catchment area as well as some parts of North Lincolnshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department has excellent facilities including:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A ten bay adult resus with individual glass fronted bays, identically equipped and same handed with new equipment throughout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A newly built, dedicated children’s area with two resuscitation rooms, 7 glass fronted cubicles and a separate waiting area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A large open plan majors area with 24 glass fronted bays and five monitored rooms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An in-department spiral CT scanner to facilitate rapid diagnosis of a range of conditions, with excellent time to CT (habitually the best in TARN)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-situ simulation exercises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent GIRFT visit had praised our capacity, infrastructure, cleanliness and attention to detail. The ED in Hull has seen a great deal of investment and support in the last few years. Our nurse staffing is in line with NICE recommendations, there is a vibrant quality improvement programme and departmental morale is really good.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will attract relocation expenses under the Trust’s policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBen RaynerJob titleClinical Director for Emergency MedicineEmail addressben.rayner@hey.nhs.ukTelephone number01482 816673&lt;/p&gt;
